#### Agent B → V-S6: "exact" Rule-Strategy auf blockId

**Statisch:**
- [ ] `matchesSelector` in `rule-matching.ts` verwendet `blockId` statt `blockIndex` im exact-Branch
- [ ] `selector.blockId` wird geprüft (statt `selector.blockIndex`)
- [ ] Typ-Definition für Exact-Selector enthält `blockId: string` (statt `blockIndex: number`)

**Verhaltens-Test** (`apps/web/src/components/format-workspace/rule-matching.test.ts`):

```ts
describe("matchesSelector — exact strategy mit blockId", () => {
  test("exact-Match mit korrekter blockId → true", () => {
    const selector = {
      strategy: "exact",
      messageId: "msg1",
      blockId: "abc12345",
      blockType: "paragraph",
    };
    expect(matchesSelector(selector, "paragraph", "text", 0, { blockId: "abc12345" })).toBe(true);
  });

  test("exact-Match mit falscher blockId → false", () => {
    const selector = {
      strategy: "exact",
      messageId: "msg1",
      blockId: "abc12345",
      blockType: "paragraph",
    };
    expect(matchesSelector(selector, "paragraph", "text", 0, { blockId: "wrong123" })).toBe(false);
  });

  test("exact-Match funktioniert unabhängig vom blockIndex", () => {
    // Der gleiche Block matcht auch wenn sein Index sich geändert hat
    const selector = { strategy: "exact", messageId: "msg1", blockId: "abc12345", blockType: "paragraph" };
    expect(matchesSelector(selector, "paragraph", "text", 0, { blockId: "abc12345" })).toBe(true);
    expect(matchesSelector(selector, "paragraph", "text", 5, { blockId: "abc12345" })).toBe(true);
  });
});
```

